				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Nerf to AE kiting<a name="17825"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 29 04 2:05 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Could you please elaborate on exactly how you are pbaoe kiting?
<br />

<br />
Here's what I have been trying (and what *did* work a few days ago, but doesn't now):
<br />

<br />
1.  Pull the big crowd.
<br />
2.  Start running backwards (hitting enter twice while running).
<br />
3.  Get crowd close together.
<br />
4.  Start playing my first pbaoe damage song, at 3/5ths of way down the spell meter, I'd start turning.  At 1/5th I'd stop turning.
<br />
5.  Repeat cycle with other two songs, playing selo's accelerando when needed.
<br />

<br />
Note-this is with a lute out, using selo's accelerando with no instrument modifiers on it (so should be the same speedfor any bard that doesn't have AA/epic/song bonus equipment on playing selo's accelerando).
<br />

<br />
This would hit them almost every time with DDD, and most of the time with the two Chords pbaoe songs.  Now it rarely hits them with any of them.
<br />

<br />
I've tried varying the time of starting and releasing the song to no avail.  If I do much more than 2/5ths of the bard while turning, the mobs will hit me.
<br />

<br />
Thanks for any information.
<br />

<br />
Temiani, 52 bard</span></td>
