				<td colspan="2"><span>As a bard of level higher than 50 with TDoK, when I go to dulak, I collect them all up, and run in the tightest possible circle.  They rarely ever touch me, but what I have noticed is that while you may run in a circle, their path tends to be more of an ellipse.  So I have had to start my songs at certain points of my circle.  And even then I don't even get all of them.
<br />

<br />
I'm not sure if that will help you any, but that is what has always worked for me on mobs with human sized attack ranges.
<br />

