				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Nerf to AE kiting<a name="17860"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 29 04 4:18 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>With run3, you just start running in a circle and start playing.  I can't really explain it better than that.  The first couple of circles, I probably don't hit many/any of the critters.  I adjust the circle til I start hitting them and once I start hitting them, I stay in my circles and keep hitting them. 
<br />

<br />
I don't change my views, I don't run backwards, I just run in a tight circle and adjust as needed to get my song to hit as many of them as possible.  
<br />

<br />
I notice that I tend to drift across the area I'm kiting in, which tells me I'm not doing circles, I'm doing weird ellipses, or a spiral. </span></td>
