				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Nerf to AE kiting<a name="17967"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 30 04 9:28 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>What was nerfed was the bug (in our favor for a change) that allowed our extended range AA to affect the AE damage songs.  It was only intended to affect our group and beneficial AE songs.  
<br />

<br />
This allowed bards a <i>really really</i> easy time kiting huge groups of critters, 40 and 50 at a time (or more), even if they had a good sized melee range.  
<br />

<br />
With the nerf, we can still AE kite, but it's a) boring as heck b) can only be done to critters with a small (human) melee range and c) only to relatively small (compared to before) sets of critters.  And, if the bard messes up, she'll get smacked around a lot, but with the smaller packs, she may live through it. ;)</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
